Caption: Figure 4. (a) A dendrogram of 36,000 laboratory generated individual particle mass spectra. The data were classified into 61 clusters are presented here in a circular hierarchical tree format. The two nodes and the 9 clusters that are the subject of this paper are identified and marked. (b) Bar graph showing the content of the 2 nodes and 9 clusters that are being re-clustered in this paper. In node A the most of the two sodium containing particles are in clusters 1. In node I 3 types of carbon containing were separated into 7 clusters one of which is strongly mixed.

Figure 6. The result of the classification of the mass spectral data of the carbon containing compounds particles (I node in Fig. 4 (a)) into 3 clusters. This classification used several sculpting techniques by the domain experts. The neighbor map is now in the particle size mode.
